{
  "texts": [
    "They found that behavioral attitudes, perceived behavioral control, and subjective norms positively influenced consumers' purchase intention.",
    "Liu (2022) discovered that the attitudes of Generation Z directly impacted their purchase intention when buying sustainable clothing.",
    "Moreover, Rausch and Kopplin (2021) study revealed that consumers' attitudes towards sustainable clothing and subjective norms significantly influenced purchase intention.",
    "At the same time, purchase intention also substantially impacts the purchase behavior of Generation Z consumers.",
    "Accordingly, this research proposes the following hypotheses in the context of green apparel purchase: H1: In the green apparel purchase behavior of Generation Z, behavioral attitudes have a positive impact on purchase intention."
  ]
}